
Eggdrop Changes (Last Updated 2026-03-09):
__________________________________________

devinkbrown fork (based on v1.10.1):

  2026-03-09 * build: optimize compiler/linker flags across all platforms:
               add -fno-strict-aliasing globally (eggdrop uses void*/char*
               casts), -pipe for faster parallel builds, -Wl,--as-needed
               on ELF platforms to drop unused library links.  New
               native-opt build option enables cpu-family-aware native
               tuning: -march=native on x86/x86_64/RISC-V/MIPS/s390x,
               -mcpu=native on ARM/AArch64/PowerPC; off by default.
               Enable LTO (b_lto=true) and strip asserts in release
               (b_ndebug=if-release) by default.
             * build: add -fvisibility=hidden to all module shared-object
               builds; update EXPORT_SCOPE in module.h to use
               __attribute__((visibility("default"))) on GCC/Clang ELF
               targets so only the module entry point is exported. Keeps
               __declspec(dllexport) for Cygwin/Windows.
             * build: remove unneeded tcl_dep/tls_dep from md5_lib (md5c.c
               uses only <string.h>); move global -DDEBUG/-g to
               add_project_arguments so they are not duplicated per target.
             * build: fix all -Wsizeof-pointer-memaccess warnings — every
               snprintf(ptr, sizeof(ptr), ...) where ptr is a char *
               parameter or nmalloc'd pointer now uses the correct buffer
               length.  Affected: filesys.mod (files.c, filesys.c,
               filedb3.c, tclfiles.c, dbcompat.c), transfer.mod
               (transfer.c, transferqueue.c, tcltransfer.c), and core
               botnet.c, language.c, misc.c.
             * build: add #undef nstrdup before the module.h redefinition
               to silence the macro-redefinition warning in every module.
             * build: add #undef _POSIX_C_SOURCE before #include <Python.h>
               in python.mod to resolve the glibc/Python 3.14 header
               conflict (202405L vs 200809L).
             [Patch by: devinkbrown]

  2026-03-08 * docs: expand README with full libop rationale — explains
               why IOCP from scratch is error-prone and what libop
               already solved (overlapped layout, stale completions,
               double-arm prevention)
             * docs: update NEWS with libop credit and rationale
             * docs: add 'Why this fork exists' and 'Why libop' sections
               to README; add BSD/macOS kqueue coverage note

  2026-03-07 * win32: stub bg.c fork/pipe/kill — bg_prepare_split(),
               bg_do_split(), bg_send_quit() are no-ops on Windows;
               bot runs in foreground with console hidden via ShowWindow
             * win32: guard sigaction block and kill(SIGCHLD) check in
               main.c with #ifndef EGG_NATIVE_WIN32
             * win32: add MOD_USE_WIN32 module-loading path using
               LoadLibraryA/GetProcAddress/FreeLibrary; meson.build
               sets MOD_USE_WIN32 before dlopen probe on Windows
             * win32: guard sys/uio.h in net.c, fcntl.h and resolv.h
               in main.c with #ifndef EGG_NATIVE_WIN32
             * build: add sys/uio.h to meson req_headers for
               HAVE_SYS_UIO_H detection
             * win32: add native Windows support — EGG_NATIVE_WIN32
               define, Winsock2/MsWSock deps, IOCP I/O backend adapted
               from libop (https://github.com/devinkbrown/ophion).
               Zero-byte overlapped WSARecv/WSASend; stale completion
               detection via slot index + socket fd recorded at arm time
             * build: replace autoconf/make with Meson + Ninja;
               optimization=2 default; -pipe flag where supported;
               per-platform dependency detection via pkg-config
             * win32: remove CYGWIN_HACKS; Cygwin retains plain POSIX
               path (select() fallback); only host_system=='windows'
               gets EGG_NATIVE_WIN32 and IOCP
             * docs: rewrite INSTALL for Meson with per-platform
               dependency steps (Debian, Fedora, macOS, MSYS2, MSVC,
               Cygwin); add MSVC/vcpkg section; document I/O backends
             * docs: update README with fork notice, build instructions,
               and I/O backend table

Eggdrop v1.10.1:

  2026-03-09 * twitch.mod: replace fixed 8191-byte mods/vips/badges/emote_sets
               buffers with dynamic char * allocations.  Each twitchchan_t
               previously wasted ~40 KB of RSS at startup regardless of
               channel content and silently truncated large mod/VIP lists.
               Memory is now allocated on first update and freed on module
               unload.  twitch_expmem() now reports actual live usage.
               [Patch by: devinkbrown]

  2026-03-09 * channels.mod/irc.mod: add mmap-backed slab allocator
               (egg_bh) for memberlist and masklist nodes.  Hot-path
               alloc/free drops from glibc malloc overhead to an
               intrusive free-list pop/push.  Memory is returned to the
               OS when a slab is destroyed rather than held in the
               malloc arena.  Typed allocator functions (channel_malloc_member,
               channel_free_member, channel_malloc_mask, channel_free_mask)
               are exported via channels_funcs[49-52] for use by irc.mod.
               [Patch by: devinkbrown]

  2026-03-09 * mem: fix n_realloc() silently returning NULL on OOM instead
               of aborting like n_malloc(); add n_strdup() / nstrdup()
               tracked by DEBUG_MEM.  Modules gain nstrdup via global[329]
               with correct MODULE_NAME attribution.
               [Patch by: devinkbrown]

  2026-03-07 * Add kqueue I/O back-end for macOS/BSD (FreeBSD, OpenBSD,
               NetBSD). Replaces select() on those platforms with a
               persistent kernel interest set that wakes only on active
               sockets, eliminating per-call fd_set rebuilds and the
               FD_SETSIZE limit. Detection via meson (sys/event.h).
               Priority chain: io_uring > epoll > kqueue > select.

